{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17568208","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17568208"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T00:11:45+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T00:11:45+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"19643"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"19643","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/19643"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.04,0.12,0.06,0.3,0.48]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"12414"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"108873"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"12414","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/12414"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"19643"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"91238"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"3"},{"type":"tags","id":"14"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"2431"},{"type":"tags","id":"4639"},{"type":"tags","id":"4955"},{"type":"tags","id":"4966"},{"type":"tags","id":"4970"},{"type":"tags","id":"4983"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11629"},{"type":"tags","id":"11643"},{"type":"tags","id":"11644"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"29604"},{"type":"contributions","id":"29605"},{"type":"contributions","id":"29606"},{"type":"contributions","id":"29607"},{"type":"contributions","id":"34957"},{"type":"contributions","id":"40639"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44438"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"108873","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/108873"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 43-year-old man presents to the General Practice clinic with a three-week history of a painless ulcer on his lower lip. He is otherwise well. He has a medical history of rheumatoid arthritis treated with methotrexate and prednisolone. His regular medications are methotrexate 15mg weekly, prednisolone 5mg daily, and folic acid. He is a current smoker with a 40 pack-year history. He is single and uses on-line dating services occasionally.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, he appears well with vital signs within normal limits. There is a well-circumscribed, firm, non-tender ulcer with raised edges on his lower lip (Image).\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate treatment?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Topical mupirocin","Oral acyclovir","Oral valaciclovir","Intramuscular benzathine penicillin","Excisional biopsy"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe clinical presentation is characteristic of a primary chancre, which requires prompt treatment to prevent progression to later stages of infection. \u003Cstrong\u003EIntramuscular benzathine penicillin\u003C/strong\u003E (2.4 million units as a single dose) is the first-line treatment, with excellent cure rates and decades of clinical experience supporting its use. This is particularly important in this immunosuppressed patient who is at higher risk of rapid progression.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOral acyclovir\u003C/strong\u003E is an antiviral medication used to treat herpes simplex virus infections. While HSV can cause oral ulcers, these are typically painful, occur in crops, and are preceded by prodromal symptoms. This medication would be ineffective against the causative organism in this case.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhile \u003Cstrong\u003Eexcisional biopsy\u003C/strong\u003E might be considered if a malignancy is suspected such as a squamous cell carcinoma or basal cell carcinoma (particularly given the patient\u0027s smoking history), the rapid onset and characteristic appearance of this painless ulcer is more consistent with primary syphilis.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOral valaciclovir\u003C/strong\u003E is a prodrug of acyclovir with better bioavailability. Like acyclovir, it would be ineffective against \u003Cem\u003ETreponema pallidum\u003C/em\u003E.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETopical mupirocin\u003C/strong\u003E is an antibiotic used for superficial skin infections. It would be ineffective against a systemic infection requiring sustained blood levels of antibiotics.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAfter initiating treatment, patients require serological monitoring to confirm cure, and all sexual contacts within the previous three months need to be traced and tested. The infection is notifiable to public health authorities. For patients with penicillin allergy, doxycycline 100mg twice daily for 14 days is an alternative treatment.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Benzathine penicillin is the first-line treatment for primary syphilis, administered as a single intramuscular dose.","Doxycycline for 14 days is an alternative in patients with penicillin allergy.","All cases of syphilis require mandatory notification and contact tracing."],"references":["Syphilis. STI Guidelines Australia. Australasian Society for HIV, Viral Hepatitis and Sexual Health Medicine (ASHM). Updated April 2024. Available from: https://sti.guidelines.org.au/sexually-transmissible-infections/syphilis/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"91238"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"19643"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"21552"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"21552","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/21552"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg"